        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 4:28PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 428 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Brevard, or near Jones Gap State Park, moving east
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Slater-Marietta, Pleasant Ridge State Park, Jones Gap State Park,
Caesars Head State Park, Dupont State Forest, Cleveland, Cedar
Mountain, and Dacusville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
